{
  "text": "Among the many studies that have considered structure functions in turbulent shear flows one notable result is the presence of a transition length scale (L s ) (Hinze 1975; [CITATION_1] . At scales larger than L s shear is considered to be important, whereas at smaller scales shear is relatively unimportant. Consequently, one expects the structure function to scale differently on either side of L s .",
